Xinhua All Media+ | Beijing Youth Ice Hockey League Helps Ignite Winter Olympics Passion - Xinhua News Network On December 11th, Pang Yaotian (center) of the Beijing Dreaming ING team shoots during a match. On that day, the 2021-2022 season Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League continued its competitions across various ice rinks in Beijing. The league is divided into regular season and playoffs, with participating athletes ranging from U6 to U18, and is organized into competitive and selection groups, attracting nearly 3,600 players from 256 teams across the city. After more than ten years of development, the Beijing Youth Ice Hockey Club League has become a platform for Beijing's young ice hockey enthusiasts to exchange skills and make friends, and provides outstanding players for the Beijing youth ice hockey team and the youth team. The league plays a leading role in promoting ice hockey among Beijing's youth, helping to fuel enthusiasm for the Winter Olympics ice hockey events, and laying the foundation for the development of ice hockey in Beijing after the Winter Olympics.
